    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-12-31T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-12-31T19:00:00-05:00" n="1122"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1122">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">841.79658/65: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-31T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >December 31, 1943—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1436. The War Department informs us that the Norwegian Government has requested
                    the British Government to proceed immediately <pb facs="1218" n="1206"
                        xml:id="pg_1206"/> to withdraw from Sweden approximately 2,000 Norwegian
                        “trainees”.<note n="23" xml:id="d1122fn23">Air crew trainees of Norwegian
                        nationality who had escaped from Norway into Sweden.</note> The British have
                    asked the American Air Transport Command to undertake the job which the latter
                    has agreed to do.</p>
                <p>The Air Transport Command is prepared to call its planes which are, in fact, Army
                    transports, civilian aircraft, to operate them with personnel not in military
                    uniform and without armament. It does not, however, desire to operate its planes
                    ostensibly or otherwise as BOAC<note n="24" xml:id="d1122fn24">British Overseas
                        Airways Corporation.</note> craft.</p>
                <p>You are requested to take up with the Swedish Government immediately the
                    conditions under which they would give their permission for American planes to
                    be operated for the purpose mentioned between Sweden and Scotland and inform us
                    as urgently as possible, as it is desired to begin these flights with the least
                    possible delay.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
